\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to define the internal culture,
 operational mindset,
 and behavioral expectations of the Elko County Information Operations Department.
 It serves as the unifying ethos that aligns individual conduct with the organizational mission—
defining how the Department leads,
 operates,
 and serves.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Information Operations personnel,
 including full-time employees,
 part-time staff,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 and volunteers.
 It governs the cultural and professional baseline for Department interactions,
 decision-making,
 and conflict resolution.
\end_layout

